On Wednesday MHD Prague will accompany you for the first time also with an electronic card
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be written in the history of the Prague Transport Company as the date on which the first passengers will climb in the metro, tram and bus instead of the paper ticket will have an electronic card in their pocket.
At this moment about one hundred thousand people who own their Opencard card can get it.
Passengers can buy the 30- and 90-day annual one (which will be valid from January 1, 2009) and at the same time have their own card charged in the Infopoints and offices of the Transport Company and at the metro station Muzeum, Můstek, Nádrží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
The coupons can already be bought yesterday on the internet at the page of the Transport Company www.dpp.cz.
More than 400 customers took advantage of the service before the afternoon.
Those who will start using the Internet service can completely forget the doors in the metro stops where they had to make long lines for paper tickets so far.
The coupon is bought via the internet and on the Opencard they charge it on one of the twelve branches of the Municipal Library.
"In these places, passengers have at their disposal a desk with trained staff that will help those interested in buying on the internet and will also record their credit on their card." said Martin Opatrný, spokesperson for the project.
In addition to the libraries it will be possible to load electronic coupons on the Opencards in ATMs and self-services that are installed at the metro entrances.
How are these ATMs?
They are red, they look like ticket obliterators and passengers have already noticed them at the metro stations Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Now there are five in the whole city but by the end of the year there should be eighty," concluded Opatrný.
The coupon will be checked instead of by the driver from the ATM.
The ATM service that will run from tomorrow is very simple.
Just enter the Opencard card and after payment of the coupon, it will load on.
The electronic cards are valid from tomorrow not only in the capital but also in its surroundings.
That is, in the urban lines of trains and buses from number 300 to 499, which the inhabitants of the municipalities of Central Bohemia take to reach the capital.
"In the integrated transport trains in Prague there are controllers equipped with card readers with which they verify the temporal and zonal validity," he explained the method of checking Filip tickets by the organization Ropid, which sets out the timetables for collective transport in Prague.
Urban buses have card readers embedded in the driver's box.
During the ascent it is therefore necessary not only to show the magnetic card to the driver, but also to place the Opencard at the determined point next to the case.
Thus the driver checks the validity of the loaded coupons.
"If the passenger needs to verify the validity of the loaded coupons, there is nothing easier than asking the driver for this type of information," Drápal added.
Passengers who take urban buses and will not remember, when the coupon expires, can again go to self-service ATMs, where the coupons are loaded on the card.
Information on the validity of their documents on the device screen will be displayed here.
The Sudeten Germans wanted a referendum from the USA
The Sudeten Germans in 1945 asked to include Šumava in the United States.
This results from the letter filed in the Southern Bohemian Scientific Library.
If we cannot be part of Germany or Austria, we want to live at least under the patronage of the United States.
