"Yes, we have a serious financial problem.
Yes, there are solutions.
But don't take advantage of the taxpayers..
Leader of a small group in the Congress nicknamed "the caucus of the skeptics," democratic representative Brad Sherman presents the situation differently, but comes to the same conclusion.
"Four hundred eminent professors of economics, including three Nobel laureates, have written to us to say: we ask Congress not to draw hasty conclusions and to examine carefully the way forward," he said yesterday.
