The psychology of excessive licitating: why spend more money?
At auctions buyers are inclined to spend more, to overestimate the goods.
Neurologists and economists researchers at the University of New York have been able to discover the neuro-economic bases of this notorious and seemingly irrational behavior.
According to their study in Science magazine, men don't want to lag behind in a race like eBay auction, so they're willing to pay even a higher price.
The research has tried to trace the nervous pattern of this "game" at the level of the nervous system through experimental auctions.
A group of volunteers played the lot, the other group of players participated in an auction while with the functional magnetic resonance method (fMRI) they examined the active areas of the brain of the participants in the experiment.
In both games the participants could win some money, but in the auction game, in which the substantial element is to lure more than the other, the striated body under the cerebral cortex comes intensively into operation when you lose to the game.
This brain area, in addition to other functions, plays a role in the "self-gratification" mechanism of the nervous system.
Thus, researchers say that the rise in price is explained by the passing of the vehement reaction of the striated body.
To support their theory, the research group economists carried out a financial follow-up survey.
In this survey, three groups filed a complaint against a partner under different conditions.
The control group was told what the real value of the product in question was and they made their bet.
To another group in addition to this they promised that in the case of winning they will receive another prize of $15.
The third group would have received $15 before the auction, but the members of the group would have lost money in the event of an auction loss.
The difference between the two groups consisted in the fact that for one of them the win was emphasized, while for the other the loss.
Recovering the neurologist hypothesis, the members of the group who played "against loss" were willing to make higher stakes than the control group or "against loss."
"These results are not deductible from any of the previously existing economic theories.
These in fact so far explained the phenomena found at the auctions with the joy of winning and avoiding risk.
Only the methods of creating the neurological image helped to resolve the contradiction between the two theories, so that we came to a third explanation," said Andrew Schotter, professor of the Faculty of Economics at the University of New York.
Hepatitis: when to seek medical advice?
Nearly half a billion people in the world suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, while chronic liver disease is mentioned among the first causes of death in Hungary.
In Hungary, the number of patients with hepatitis is one hundred thousand, of whom only 7000 are treated: the reason is that many patients do not know they are infected.
The hepatitis definition is the collective name of contagious liver disease caused by several viruses.
There are many similarities between the symptoms, typical are hepatitis and jaundice, but their pathogens and diseases caused differ from each other.
Hepatitis viruses spread in two main forms depending on the pathogen: hepatitis A and E via the food channel (e.g. water and infected food), hepatitis B, C, D and other viruses with blood and organic fluids (sperm, vaginal leaks, saliva).
For travelers it is useful to vaccination against virus A and B, against C there is no vaccine.
Symptoms of hepatitis A appear two to three weeks after consumption of infected foods, accompanied by general malaise, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After yellowish spots are formed on the skin and on the white of the eyes, the faeces become clear and the urine dark, the healing takes place within two to three weeks.
One million people die every year worldwide for hepatitis B, the most serious variant of the disease, which causes liver cancers and cirrhosis of the liver.
The main reason is, according to estimates, that only one in ten people receive a pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: if it is not treated, it can cause cirrhosis of the liver and liver cancers.
Most infected people do not know that they have contracted the disease because pathogens deviously destroy liver cells, in many cases the first symptoms appear after 20-30 years.
Therefore it is very important to prevent and carry out regular medical tests.
This disease is much more frequent than average in three groups: those who had a blood transfusion before 1991, drug addicts and tattooed.
Worldwide, the number of people infected with chronic hepatitis C virus amounts to 200 million.
Since even a routine laboratory test reveals the disease it is worth asking your family doctor when you notice any symptoms of unknown origin.
Recognized in time the disease is curable, the virus can be eliminated from the body, thus stops the infectious power and can be prevented the formation of tumors.
September 30 is the world's day of hepatitis, organized for the first time in 2004 by patient associations around the world.
The aim is to draw attention to chronic viral hepatitis, the causes of its development and the early recognition of the disease.
Who believes in God feels less pain?
According to the result of a recent investigation, religious faith functions as a kind of analgesic that has made the death of Catholic martyrs more bearable.
Scientists at Oxford University performed an interesting experiment, examining how faith in God affects the feeling of pain, reported the British Telegraph.
As part of the somewhat bizarre investigation, an electroshock was carried out to 12 Catholic believers and as many atheists, while all of them observed a painting depicting the virgin Mary.
According to the results, Catholic believers were able to reject much of the pain.
Thanks to the exploratory technique of the human brain it was discovered that Catholics were able to activate the part of the brain responsible for the control of pain.
The test is the first in a series of researches in which in addition to academics also participate scientists, philosophers and theologians of the University.
The test was carried out exactly like this: an instrument that emits discharges and passes the electroshock was connected to the left hand of the subject of the experiment.
The researchers asked the participants to focus on two paintings, the virgin Mary painted in the seventeenth century by Sassoferrato and the Lady with the ermine of Leonardo da Vinci painted in the fifteenth century.
The authors of the examination hoped that the image of the Virgin Mary would give rise to a sort of religious state among believers, while Leonardo's painting was chosen because it did not differ too much from the other and considered it to have a calming effect.
The subjects of the experiment spent half an hour in front of the MRI scanner and in this time they received 20 electroshocks in four consecutive series, while they observed either the religious-themed painting or the other.
Catholics reported that the vision of the virgin Mary made them feel "safe" as if "someone cared for them" and "relaxed and were pervaded by peace."
Looking at the religious-themed image, they accounted for 12% less pain than when Leonardo's work was before them.
The psychologist Miguel Farias, who took part in the test himself, believes that such a result can be achieved with any image with a strong effect even for atheists, but you have to find the right image.
"We need to look for an image to which they have very positive feelings, such as a mother or father," said the psychologist.
Anglican bishop Tom Wright welcomed the result of the research.
"The practice of faith should change, and in many cases it can change our personality." - added Wright.
After the excellent results only the question remains whether the painting of a Madonna of Leonardo or another painter of such caliber is presented to believers, what effect could it have on the control of pain?
Would the vision of a quality virgin Mary bring better results?
