Industry prices continue to rise
National industrial sales prices in August 2008 increased by 0.1% compared to the previous month, by 12.9% compared to August 2007 - reports the Hungarian Central Statistical Institute.
The export sales prices of the industry reported in July 2008 were 1.1% higher, compared to the previous year they decreased by 3.9%.
As a result of the change in domestic and export prices, industrial production costs were 0.7% higher than in the previous month and 3.2% higher than in a year ago.
The prices of domestic industrial sales in relation to the previous month increased by only 0,1%.
Prices of domestic sales in the processing sector also rose to a minimum of 0.1% compared with July.
The largest increase in prices in August 2008 occurred in the leather and shoe processing sector (2.8%), especially the bags and belts with 4.6% and the production of shoes with 2.5% monthly increase.
The high price level of plastics and chemicals has led to a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the product and chemical sector.
Price reductions occurred in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electrical instruments and machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum extent in wood processing (0.1%)
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing have not changed.
In the other sectors of the processing industry there was an increase in prices between 0.2 and 0.9%.
In the field of electricity, gas, steam and water supply, prices increased in August by 0.3% in domestic industrial sales, firstly as a result of the dominant effect of the increase in gas prices by the authorities since 1 July.
Compared in 12 months, considering the domestic sales of the processing industry, the largest increases were in the oil processing sector (32.4%).
In the manufacture of metalworking products, price increases were 13.2%, 11% in the production of food, beverages and tobacco, representing a decisive weight.
Prices fell in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the production of electrical instruments and machinery (0.3%).
In the other sectors of the processing industry, the rate of price increases varied from 0.6% to 9.1%.
Total prices in the processing industry in the past year rose by 10.2%.
Prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector exceeded 18.7% of last year's prices.
In domestic sales among target groups in the sectors, the largest increase in monthly prices occurred in August in the sectors producing investment goods (0.7%).
In the sectors producing consumer items, prices have risen by 0.3%, in the energy sector and in the subsequent use, prices have not changed compared to those of the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to the same month last year, the largest price increase was observed in the energy sector and subsequent use (16.8%).
In the sectors producing consumer articles, the increase was 6.8%, for investment goods a decrease of 1.4% was measured.
Industrial export sales prices in guilders increased by 1.1% in August compared to the previous month, compared with 12 months, by 3.9%.
The Hungarian guilder has weakened in a month compared to the euro by 1.7%, compared to the dollar by 7.1%, compared with August 2007 by 7.5% compared to the euro and 15.9% against the dollar.
