Today in Paris began the European Summit for Equal Opportunities, organized this year by France with the presidency of the European Union.
Lívia Járóka, Fidesz Member of the European People's Party, in her message to the Plenum as the main rapporteur of the Congress, drew attention to school segregation because it is the most serious legal violation affecting Roma children and also the most serious obstacle to their affirmation.
Mr Xavier Bertrand, French Minister for Employment and Social Affairs, on behalf of the French Presidency, and Mr Vladimír Špidla, European Commissioner for Employment, Social Affairs and Equal Opportunities, opened the conference at the highest level.
